cs.IT, cs.COMM, cs.SI, cs.NI, cs.MM 

This paper deals with information theory and communication systems, specifically the AWGN broadcast channel with receiver message side information. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also involves communication systems, which suggests cs.COMM (Communications and Networking) as a likely sub-category. The use of side information is a key aspect of the paper, which could place it in cs.SI (Signal Processing and Information Theory) or cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Finally, the paper proposes inner and outer bounds, which could also place it in cs.MM (Multimedia).
